<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Iron Endurance — May–October 2025 v5</title>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Barlow+Condensed:wght@400;600;700;800;900&family=Mulish:ital,wght@0,300;0,400;0,600;1,300&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
:root{
  --bg:#0c0e11;--s1:#141720;--s2:#1b1f2a;--s3:#222836;
  --bd:#2a3040;--tx:#c8d0de;--td:#7a8499;--tf:#3c4558;--wh:#e8edf4;
  --fire:#e05520;--gold:#c49828;--grn:#2e9660;--blu:#2878b8;--red:#b83030;--yel:#c8a000;--purp:#8855cc;
}
*{margin:0;padding:0;box-sizing:border-box;}
body{background:var(--bg);color:var(--tx);font-family:'Mulish',sans-serif;font-weight:300;line-height:1.7;}
nav{position:sticky;top:0;z-index:500;background:rgba(12,14,17,0.97);backdrop-filter:blur(14px);border-bottom:1px solid var(--bd);display:flex;align-items:stretch;padding:0 24px;overflow-x:auto;scrollbar-width:none;}
nav::-webkit-scrollbar{display:none;}
.nbrand{font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:900;font-size:1rem;letter-spacing:0.2em;color:var(--fire);display:flex;align-items:center;padding-right:20px;margin-right:6px;border-right:1px solid var(--bd);white-space:nowrap;}
.nb{background:none;border:none;color:var(--td);font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.62rem;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;padding:15px 12px;cursor:pointer;white-space:nowrap;border-bottom:2px solid transparent;transition:color .15s,border-color .15s;}
.nb:hover{color:var(--wh);}.nb.on{color:var(--fire);border-bottom-color:var(--fire);}
.hero{max-width:1100px;margin:0 auto;padding:68px 36px 48px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--bd);}
.hero-eye{font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.62rem;letter-spacing:0.24em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--fire);margin-bottom:12px;}
.hero h1{font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:900;font-size:clamp(3rem,10vw,6.5rem);line-height:0.87;color:var(--wh);margin-bottom:18px;}
.hero h1 em{color:var(--fire);font-style:normal;}
.hero-desc{font-size:0.9rem;color:var(--td);max-width:660px;line-height:1.82;margin-bottom:32px;}
.statbar{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:1px;background:var(--bd);border:1px solid var(--bd);max-width:820px;}
.sc{background:var(--s1);padding:13px 18px;flex:1;min-width:86px;}
.sc-l{font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.52rem;letter-spacing:0.15em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--tf);margin-bottom:3px;}
.sc-v{font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:700;font-size:1.5rem;color:var(--gold);}
.sec{display:none;max-width:1100px;margin:0 auto;padding:50px 36px;}
.sec.on{display:block;}
.sh{display:flex;align-items:baseline;gap:14px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--bd);padding-bottom:12px;margin-bottom:24px;}
.sh h2{font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:800;font-size:1.9rem;letter-spacing:0.04em;color:var(--wh);}
.sh-tag{font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.58rem;letter-spacing:0.14em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--fire);}
.phases{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(145px,1fr));gap:2px;background:var(--bd);margin-bottom:26px;}
.ph{background:var(--s1);padding:15px 14px;cursor:pointer;transition:background .15s;border-left:3px solid transparent;}
.ph:hover{background:var(--s2);}.ph.ap{background:var(--s2);border-left-color:var(--fire);}
.ph-n{font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.52rem;letter-spacing:0.14em;color:var(--tf);margin-bottom:3px;}
.ph-t{font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:700;font-size:1.04rem;letter-spacing:0.04em;color:var(--wh);margin-bottom:1px;}
.ph-d{font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.57rem;color:var(--fire);margin-bottom:5px;}
.ph-i{font-size:0.74rem;color:var(--td);line-height:1.55;}
.al{padding:14px 20px;margin-bottom:13px;font-size:0.84rem;line-height:1.78;color:var(--tx);border-left:3px solid;}
.al h4{font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:700;font-size:1rem;letter-spacing:0.04em;margin-bottom:7px;}
.al ul{list-style:none;}.al ul li{padding:2px 0;}.al ul li::before{content:"→ ";color:var(--fire);}
.al-fire{background:rgba(224,85,32,0.08);border-color:var(--fire);}
.al-gold{background:rgba(196,152,40,0.08);border-color:var(--gold);}
.al-grn{background:rgba(46,150,96,0.08);border-color:var(--grn);}
.al-blu{background:rgba(40,120,184,0.08);border-color:var(--blu);}
.al-red{background:rgba(184,48,48,0.08);border-color:var(--red);}
.al-purp{background:rgba(136,85,204,0.08);border-color:var(--purp);}
.pbrow{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:6px;margin-bottom:16px;}
.pb{background:var(--s2);border:1px solid var(--bd);color:var(--td);font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.62rem;padding:7px 13px;cursor:pointer;letter-spacing:0.08em;transition:all .15s;}
.pb:hover{border-color:var(--fire);color:var(--wh);}.pb.on{background:var(--fire);border-color:var(--fire);color:#fff;}
.pd{display:none;}.pd.on{display:block;}
.wtabs{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:5px;margin-bottom:16px;}
.wt{background:var(--s3);border:1px solid var(--bd);color:var(--td);font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.58rem;padding:6px 12px;cursor:pointer;letter-spacing:0.07em;transition:all .15s;}
.wt:hover{border-color:var(--gold);color:var(--wh);}.wt.on{background:var(--gold);border-color:var(--gold);color:#0c0e11;}
.wd{display:none;}.wd.on{display:block;}
.pi{background:var(--s2);border-left:3px solid var(--gold);padding:13px 18px;margin-bottom:18px;font-size:0.84rem;color:var(--td);line-height:1.78;}
.pi strong{color:var(--wh);}
.wk-banner{background:var(--s3);border:1px solid var(--bd);border-left:4px solid var(--fire);padding:10px 16px;margin-bottom:14px;display:flex;align-items:baseline;gap:12px;flex-wrap:wrap;}
.wk-title{font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:800;font-size:1.15rem;letter-spacing:0.06em;color:var(--wh);}
.wk-note{font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.57rem;color:var(--td);text-transform:uppercase;}
.wk-loads{font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.62rem;color:var(--fire);margin-left:auto;text-align:right;line-height:1.7;}
.daygrid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(285px,1fr));gap:12px;margin-bottom:24px;}
.dc{background:var(--s1);border:1px solid var(--bd);}
.dch{padding:11px 18px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--bd);display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:8px;}
.dcn{font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:700;font-size:1.02rem;letter-spacing:0.06em;color:var(--wh);}
.badge{font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.52rem;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;padding:3px 8px;white-space:nowrap;}
.b-lift{background:rgba(224,85,32,0.14);color:var(--fire);}
.b-oly{background:rgba(196,152,40,0.14);color:var(--gold);}
.b-cardio{background:rgba(46,150,96,0.14);color:var(--grn);}
.b-shift{background:rgba(200,160,0,0.18);color:var(--yel);}
.b-sprint{background:rgba(184,48,48,0.14);color:var(--red);}
.b-golf{background:rgba(40,120,184,0.14);color:var(--blu);}
.b-beach{background:rgba(136,85,204,0.14);color:var(--purp);}
.b-bench{background:rgba(224,85,32,0.22);color:#ff8855;}
.dcb{padding:14px 18px;}
.xt{width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;font-size:0.79rem;}
.xt th{font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.52rem;letter-spacing:0.12em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--tf);text-align:left;padding:0 6px 7px 0;border-bottom:1px solid var(--bd);}
.xt td{padding:6px 6px 6px 0;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(42,48,64,0.5);vertical-align:top;}
.xt tr:last-child td{border-bottom:none;}
.xn{color:var(--tx);}.xl{font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.7rem;color:var(--fire) !important;}
.xnote{font-size:0.71rem;color:var(--td);font-style:italic;}
.dnote{font-size:0.73rem;color:var(--tf);font-style:italic;margin-top:9px;padding-top:9px;border-top:1px solid var(--bd);line-height:1.65;}
.prog-box{background:var(--s2);border:1px solid var(--bd);padding:14px 18px;margin-bottom:18px;}
.prog-box h5{font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:700;font-size:0.95rem;letter-spacing:0.05em;color:var(--gold);margin-bottom:10px;}
.prog-table{width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;font-size:0.78rem;}
.prog-table th{font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.52rem;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--tf);text-align:left;padding:5px 8px 5px 0;border-bottom:1px solid var(--bd);}
.prog-table td{padding:5px 8px 5px 0;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(42,48,64,0.4);color:var(--td);}
.prog-table tr:last-child td{border-bottom:none;}
.pw{font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;color:var(--gold);font-size:0.71rem;}
.pv{font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;color:var(--fire);font-size:0.71rem;}
.grid2{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(250px,1fr));gap:13px;margin-bottom:28px;}
.card{background:var(--s1);border:1px solid var(--bd);padding:22px;}
.card-tag{font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.55rem;letter-spacing:0.14em;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:8px;}
.card h3{font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:700;font-size:1.25rem;letter-spacing:0.04em;color:var(--wh);margin-bottom:7px;}
.card p{font-size:0.83rem;color:var(--td);line-height:1.75;}
.t-fire{color:var(--fire);}.t-gold{color:var(--gold);}.t-grn{color:var(--grn);}.t-blu{color:var(--blu);}.t-wh{color:var(--wh);}.t-purp{color:var(--purp);}
.dt{width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin-bottom:22px;}
.dt th{font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.57rem;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--tf);text-align:left;padding:9px 12px;border-bottom:2px solid var(--bd);background:var(--s2);}
.dt td{padding:9px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--bd);font-size:0.83rem;color:var(--td);}
.dt tr:nth-child(even) td{background:rgba(20,23,32,0.45);}
.dt-n{color:var(--wh) !important;}.dt-v{font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;color:var(--gold) !important;}
.lg{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(235px,1fr));gap:13px;}
.lc{background:var(--s1);border:1px solid var(--bd);padding:20px;}
.lc h3{font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:700;font-size:1.1rem;letter-spacing:0.05em;margin-bottom:11px;}
.lc ul{list-style:none;font-size:0.81rem;color:var(--td);line-height:1.9;}
.lc ul li::before{content:"· ";color:var(--fire);font-weight:bold;}
.bcbar{background:var(--s1);border:1px solid var(--bd);padding:16px 20px;margin-bottom:11px;}
.bcl{font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.57rem;letter-spacing:0.12em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--tf);margin-bottom:5px;}
.bct{height:8px;background:var(--s3);border-radius:2px;overflow:hidden;margin-bottom:5px;}
.bcf{height:100%;border-radius:2px;}
.bcn{font-size:0.77rem;color:var(--td);}
.change-tag{display:inline-block;font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.54rem;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;padding:2px 7px;background:rgba(196,152,40,0.15);color:var(--gold);border:1px solid rgba(196,152,40,0.3);margin-left:8px;}
@media(max-width:620px){.hero{padding:48px 18px 34px;}.sec{padding:36px 18px;}.phases{grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;}nav{padding:0 10px;}}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<nav>
  <div class="nbrand">Iron Endurance</div>
  <button class="nb on" onclick="S('overview',this)">Overview</button>
  <button class="nb" onclick="S('workouts',this)">Workouts</button>
  <button class="nb" onclick="S('loads',this)">Loads & %</button>
  <button class="nb" onclick="S('spine',this)">Back Protocol</button>
  <button class="nb" onclick="S('cardio',this)">Cardio & Sprints</button>
  <button class="nb" onclick="S('nutrition',this)">Nutrition</button>
</nav>
<div class="hero">
  <div class="hero-eye">Custom Program · May–October 2025 · 26 yrs · Every Week Written · Full Progressions</div>
  <h1>IRON<br><em>ENDURANCE</em></h1>
  <p class="hero-desc">Every week is written individually. Every percentage and RPE is listed. What changes each week is highlighted so you can find it instantly without re-reading the whole session. Firefighter. Olympic lifter. Powerlifter. Golfer. 26 yrs. Physio 1–2×/wk.</p>
  <div class="statbar">
    <div class="sc"><div class="sc-l">Snatch</div><div class="sc-v">215</div></div>
    <div class="sc"><div class="sc-l">C&amp;J</div><div class="sc-v">285</div></div>
    <div class="sc"><div class="sc-l">Squat</div><div class="sc-v">415</div></div>
    <div class="sc"><div class="sc-l">Bench</div><div class="sc-v">320→+</div></div>
    <div class="sc"><div class="sc-l">Deadlift</div><div class="sc-v">435</div></div>
    <div class="sc"><div class="sc-l">Body Fat</div><div class="sc-v">~16%</div></div>
    <div class="sc"><div class="sc-l">BF Target</div><div class="sc-v">13%</div></div>
    <div class="sc"><div class="sc-l">Age</div><div class="sc-v">26</div></div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- OVERVIEW -->
<div id="overview" class="sec on">
  <div class="sh"><h2>Program Architecture</h2><span class="sh-tag">5 Blocks · 26 Weeks · May–October</span></div>
  <div class="phases">
    <div class="ph ap" onclick="gP('p1')"><div class="ph-n">Block 01</div><div class="ph-t">Deload + Recomp</div><div class="ph-d">May · Wks 1–2</div><div class="ph-i">CNS reset. Full Oly 58–65%. Deficit starts. Beach muscle intro.</div></div>
    <div class="ph" onclick="gP('p2')"><div class="ph-n">Block 02</div><div class="ph-t">Build + Early Golf</div><div class="ph-d">May Wk3–June · 6 wks</div><div class="ph-i">4 sessions/wk. Oly singles + back-offs. Bench focus. Golf 3–4×/wk.</div></div>
    <div class="ph" onclick="gP('p3')"><div class="ph-n">Block 03</div><div class="ph-t">Peak Golf · Maintain</div><div class="ph-d">July–August · 9 wks</div><div class="ph-i">Golf 5×/wk. 3 gym sessions. Full Oly stays. Bench every week.</div></div>
    <div class="ph" onclick="gP('p4')"><div class="ph-n">Block 04</div><div class="ph-t">Wind-Down + Push</div><div class="ph-d">September · 4 wks</div><div class="ph-i">Golf 4×/wk. 4 gym sessions. Oly loads climb. Bench near-max.</div></div>
    <div class="ph" onclick="gP('p5')"><div class="ph-n">Block 05</div><div class="ph-t">Strength Rebuild</div><div class="ph-d">October · 4 wks</div><div class="ph-i">Golf ends. 5 sessions/wk. Conv. DL returns. Max prep November.</div></div>
  </div>
  <div class="al al-purp">
    <h4>How to Read This Program</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Select a block → select a week tab. Every week has its own complete sessions written out.</li>
      <li>When 2–3 consecutive weeks share the same percentages, one set of sessions is shown. The next week's tab shows only a <span class="change-tag">↑ CHANGE</span> table listing exactly what increases — you don't re-read the full session.</li>
      <li>Oly lifts show both a % target and an RPE. Build to the % as a guide; use RPE 8–8.5 as your stop point. If you hit RPE 8.5 before the target %, take that lift — don't chase the number.</li>
      <li>Station workout (on shift) and golf day order of operations are written in full in Block 1, Week 1. They are identical every block — reference Block 1 whenever needed.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="al al-fire">
    <h4>Oly Lifting — The Real Rules</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Full squat snatch and squat clean from day one. Your back hurts from golf rotation, not lifting. Winter training confirms this.</li>
      <li>Every Oly session: build systematically to a heavy single at the listed RPE, then hit back-off sets at the listed %. Back-offs drop from 3 sets to 2 during peak golf (Block 3) and return to 3 in Block 4.</li>
      <li>If SIJ is irritated that specific week: hang positions only for that week. Short-term adjustment, not a permanent rule.</li>
      <li>Physio 1–2×/wk is a significant asset. Tell them what you lifted and what you felt. Their real-time feedback beats any percentage table.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="al al-gold">
    <h4>Bench Arc — 320 → 335–345 by November</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>2 bench exposures every week in every block without exception — one heavy/intensity day, one volume/accessory day.</li>
      <li>Key drivers: floor press (raw strength), Spoto press (bottom strength), weighted dips (lockout), close-grip bench (tricep). All listed with specific % each week.</li>
      <li>Bench does NOT reduce during golf season. Zero SIJ demand. This is where you keep improving all summer.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="al al-grn">
    <h4>Shift Logic</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Shift day: station workout — upper + core + 20 min Zone 2. McGill Big 3 always first.</li>
      <li>Day after shift: Zone 2 only or full rest. No heavy iron within 16 hrs of shift end.</li>
      <li>2 days after shift: best heavy session. Schedule Oly and squat work here.</li>
      <li>Week-off rotation block: push 5 sessions. That is your highest volume week — use it.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- WORKOUTS -->
<div id="workouts" class="sec">
  <div class="sh"><h2>Weekly Workouts</h2><span class="sh-tag">Every Week Written · Select Block → Week Tab</span></div>
  <div class="pbrow">
    <button class="pb on" onclick="sP('p1',this)">Blk 1 — Deload (2 wks)</button>
    <button class="pb" onclick="sP('p2',this)">Blk 2 — Build (6 wks)</button>
    <button class="pb" onclick="sP('p3',this)">Blk 3 — Peak Golf (9 wks)</button>
    <button class="pb" onclick="sP('p4',this)">Blk 4 — Wind-Down (4 wks)</button>
    <button class="pb" onclick="sP('p5',this)">Blk 5 — Rebuild (4 wks)</button>
  </div>

<!-- ██ BLOCK 1 ██ -->
<div id="p1" class="pd on">
<div class="pi"><strong>Block 1 — Deload & Recomp Launch · May Weeks 1–2</strong><br>
You just maxed out. CNS needs 10–14 days sub-65%. Loads are low because of the maxout — not your back. Start caloric deficit now. Lock in McGill Big 3 as a daily habit. 2 lift sessions/wk + station on shift + 3 standalone cardio sessions. Golf starts 3×/wk mid-May.</div>
<div class="wtabs">
  <button class="wt on" onclick="sW('p1','w1',this)">Week 1</button>
  <button class="wt" onclick="sW('p1','w2',this)">Week 2</button>
</div>

<div id="p1-w1" class="wd on">
<div class="wk-banner">
  <div class="wk-title">Week 1 — True Deload</div>
  <div class="wk-note">Sessions under 50 min · Nothing close to failure</div>
  <div class="wk-loads">Snatch 58% (125) · C&amp;J 60% (171) · Squat 55% (228) · Bench 62% (198) · TBD 50% (228)</div>
</div>
<div class="daygrid">
<div class="dc">
  <div class="dch"><div class="dcn">Session A — Full Oly + Lower</div><div class="badge b-oly">58–60% · RPE 5</div></div>
  <div class="dcb">
    <div style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--grn);margin-bottom:10px;font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;">⚑ McGill Big 3 + Hip 90/90 mobility — BEFORE every single session, every block, all program long</div>
    <table class="xt">
      <tr><th>Exercise</th><th>Sets × Reps</th><th>Load</th><th>RPE</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Snatch (full squat)</td><td>5 × 3</td><td class="xl">58% = 125 lb</td><td class="xnote">RPE 5</td><td class="xnote">Full catch. Technique focus. Perfect reps only.</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Clean &amp; Jerk (squat clean)</td><td>5 × 2+1</td><td class="xl">60% = 171 lb</td><td class="xnote">RPE 5</td><td class="xnote">Full squat catch. Reset jerk each rep.</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Back Squat</td><td>4 × 6</td><td class="xl">55% = 228 lb</td><td class="xnote">RPE 5</td><td class="xnote">Deliberate, controlled. Not grinding.</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Trap Bar Deadlift</td><td>3 × 8</td><td class="xl">50% = 228 lb</td><td class="xnote">RPE 4–5</td><td class="xnote">Trap bar only through all of golf season</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Banded Clamshell</td><td>3 × 15 ea</td><td class="xl">Band</td><td class="xnote">—</td><td class="xnote">Glute activation — every session all program</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Pallof Press</td><td>3 × 12 ea</td><td class="xl">Band/Cable</td><td class="xnote">—</td><td class="xnote">Anti-rotation, brace before each rep</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Bird Dog</td><td>3 × 8 ea</td><td class="xl">BW</td><td class="xnote">—</td><td class="xnote">2-second hold at full extension</td></tr>
    </table>
    <div class="dnote">45 min max. Trap bar DL estimated ~10% above conventional — test conservatively in Week 2.</div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="dc">
  <div class="dch"><div class="dcn">Session B — Bench + Hypertrophy</div><div class="badge b-bench">62% Volume · RPE 6</div></div>
  <div class="dcb">
    <table class="xt">
      <tr><th>Exercise</th><th>Sets × Reps</th><th>Load</th><th>RPE</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Bench Press</td><td>4 × 8</td><td class="xl">62% = 198 lb</td><td class="xnote">RPE 6</td><td class="xnote">Volume week. Rebuild work capacity post-max.</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Weighted Dips</td><td>3 × 10</td><td class="xl">Moderate</td><td class="xnote">RPE 6</td><td class="xnote">Chest dip, full ROM</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">DB Incline Press</td><td>3 × 12</td><td class="xl">Moderate</td><td class="xnote">RPE 6</td><td class="xnote">Full stretch at bottom</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Cable or DB Fly</td><td>3 × 15</td><td class="xl">Light-Mod</td><td class="xnote">RPE 6</td><td class="xnote">Chest pump, squeeze at top</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">EZ Bar Curl</td><td>3 × 12</td><td class="xl">Moderate</td><td class="xnote">RPE 6</td><td class="xnote">Controlled eccentric</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Hammer Curl</td><td>3 × 12</td><td class="xl">Moderate</td><td class="xnote">RPE 6</td><td class="xnote">Brachialis focus</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Overhead Tricep Extension</td><td>3 × 15</td><td class="xl">Moderate</td><td class="xnote">RPE 6</td><td class="xnote">Long head priority</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">DB Lateral Raise</td><td>4 × 15</td><td class="xl">Light</td><td class="xnote">RPE 6</td><td class="xnote">Slow, controlled, no swinging</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Face Pull</td><td>3 × 20</td><td class="xl">Band</td><td class="xnote">—</td><td class="xnote">End every session with this — always</td></tr>
    </table>
    <div class="dnote">Zero SIJ risk. Zero spinal loading. This is your beach muscle day.</div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="dc">
  <div class="dch"><div class="dcn">Station Workout (On Shift)</div><div class="badge b-shift">Hall Gym · Every Shift · All Program</div></div>
  <div class="dcb">
    <table class="xt">
      <tr><th>Exercise</th><th>Sets × Reps</th><th>Load</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">McGill Big 3</td><td>2 rounds</td><td class="xl">BW</td><td class="xnote">Always first</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Pull-Up (weighted if available)</td><td>5 × 5</td><td class="xl">BW+</td><td class="xnote">Dead hang start and finish</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Push-Up or Dip</td><td>4 × 15</td><td class="xl">BW+</td><td class="xnote">Chest volume</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Single-Arm DB Row</td><td>4 × 10 ea</td><td class="xl">Moderate</td><td class="xnote">Brace core</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Copenhagen Plank</td><td>3 × 20s ea</td><td class="xl">BW</td><td class="xnote">Lateral core + adductor</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Half-Kneeling Pallof Press</td><td>3 × 12 ea</td><td class="xl">Band</td><td class="xnote">Anti-rotation</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Assault Bike or Row Erg</td><td>20 min</td><td class="xl">Zone 2</td><td class="xnote">130–142 bpm easy</td></tr>
    </table>
    <div class="dnote">Station workout identical every block. No heavy lower body on shift — SCBA work already loads lumbar.</div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="dc">
  <div class="dch"><div class="dcn">Standalone Cardio × 3/wk</div><div class="badge b-cardio">Zone 2 · 22–25 min</div></div>
  <div class="dcb">
    <table class="xt">
      <tr><th>Activity</th><th>Duration</th><th>HR</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Outdoor run</td><td>22–25 min</td><td class="xl">130–140 bpm</td><td class="xnote">Preferred. Conversational pace.</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Outdoor bike (if SIJ sore)</td><td>30–35 min</td><td class="xl">130–140 bpm</td><td class="xnote">Zero impact alternative</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Hip flexor stretch after</td><td>90s ea</td><td class="xl">—</td><td class="xnote">Every cardio day</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">McGill Big 3 after</td><td>6 min</td><td class="xl">—</td><td class="xnote">Build the daily habit now</td></tr>
    </table>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="dc">
  <div class="dch"><div class="dcn">Golf Day — Order of Operations</div><div class="badge b-golf">Every Round · Every Block · All Program</div></div>
  <div class="dcb">
    <table class="xt">
      <tr><th>Step</th><th>Activity</th><th>Time</th><th>Why</th></tr>
      <tr><td class="xnote">1</td><td class="xn">90/90 Hip Stretch</td><td>2 min ea</td><td class="xnote">Passive hip opening — rotation from hip, not SI joint</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xnote">2</td><td class="xn">Hip CARs (standing circles)</td><td>3 circles ea</td><td class="xnote">Active joint prep, full range</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xnote">3</td><td class="xn">Glute Bridge × 20</td><td>1 set</td><td class="xnote">Fire SIJ stabilizers before 80 swings</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xnote">4</td><td class="xn">Half-Kneeling T-Spine Rotation</td><td>10 ea</td><td class="xnote">Thoracic rotates so lumbar doesn't</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xnote">5</td><td class="xn">Golf (walk 18 holes)</td><td>Full round</td><td class="xnote">Primary summer Zone 2 cardio</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xnote">6</td><td class="xn">Post-round decompression</td><td>10 min</td><td class="xnote">Back Protocol tab — mandatory every round</td></tr>
    </table>
    <div class="dnote">No gym on golf days. Station workout on shift days is how training frequency stays without stacking golf + gym.</div>
  </div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

