<!-- ██ BLOCK 2 ██ -->
<div id="p2" class="pd">
<div class="pi"><strong>Block 2 — Build + Early Golf · May Wk3 – June · 6 Weeks</strong><br>
4 gym sessions/wk + station on shift. Full squat Oly heavy singles begin with back-offs. Bench gets both a heavy day and a volume day. Hypertrophy day stays. Golf 3→4 rounds/wk. Same % for 2 weeks, then a jump. Away trip in June = full rest.</div>
<div class="wtabs">
  <button class="wt on" onclick="sW('p2','w12',this)">Wks 1–2</button>
  <button class="wt" onclick="sW('p2','w34',this)">Wks 3–4</button>
  <button class="wt" onclick="sW('p2','w56',this)">Wks 5–6</button>
</div>

<div id="p2-w12" class="wd on">
<div class="wk-banner">
  <div class="wk-title">Weeks 1–2 (May Wk3–4) — First Build</div>
  <div class="wk-note">Run both weeks at these exact numbers</div>
  <div class="wk-loads">Snatch ~83% feel → 3×2 @ 74% (159) · C&amp;J ~83% feel → 3×2 @ 74% (211) · Squat 5×5 @ 70% (291) · Bench ~83% feel → 4×3 @ 76% (243) · TBD 4×5 @ 68% (309)</div>
</div>
<div class="al al-blu" style="margin-bottom:14px;"><h4>Block 2 Weekly Structure</h4><ul>
  <li><strong>Session A (2 days post-shift):</strong> Snatch + Squat — heaviest session of the week</li>
  <li><strong>Session B (next off day):</strong> Bench heavy + floor press + upper accessories</li>
  <li><strong>Shift day:</strong> Station workout — upper + core + Zone 2</li>
  <li><strong>Session C (2 days post-shift or off day):</strong> C&amp;J + Trap Bar DL + Pull</li>
  <li><strong>Session D (off day):</strong> Hypertrophy + Arms + Beach</li>
  <li><strong>Cardio 2×/wk:</strong> 28–35 min Zone 2 run or bike, post-shift or lighter off days</li>
  <li><strong>Golf 3–4×/wk:</strong> Pre-round warmup every time. No gym same day as golf.</li>
</ul></div>
<div class="daygrid">
<div class="dc">
  <div class="dch"><div class="dcn">Session A — Snatch + Squat</div><div class="badge b-oly">Single ~83% feel / RPE 8 → 3×2 @ 74%</div></div>
  <div class="dcb">
    <table class="xt">
      <tr><th>Exercise</th><th>Sets × Reps</th><th>Load</th><th>RPE</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Snatch — build to heavy single</td><td>Warm-up + 1 single</td><td class="xl">~83% feel ≈ 178 lb</td><td class="xnote">RPE 8 — stop here</td><td class="xnote">Build in 10–15 lb jumps. Stop when bar slows or RPE 8. Leave 1 rep in tank.</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Snatch — back-off sets</td><td>3 × 2</td><td class="xl">74% = 159 lb</td><td class="xnote">RPE 7</td><td class="xnote">Should feel smooth and fast after the heavy single</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Snatch Pull</td><td>4 × 4</td><td class="xl">90% of single ≈ 160 lb</td><td class="xnote">RPE 7</td><td class="xnote">Lat tension, aggressive extension</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Back Squat</td><td>5 × 5</td><td class="xl">70% = 291 lb</td><td class="xnote">RPE 7</td><td class="xnote">Volume day — bar moves with speed</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Front Squat (pause 2s)</td><td>3 × 4</td><td class="xl">63% = 214 lb</td><td class="xnote">RPE 6</td><td class="xnote">Jerk receiving position strength</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Suitcase Carry 30m</td><td>4 rounds</td><td class="xl">Heavy</td><td class="xnote">—</td><td class="xnote">Lateral stabilizer — golf and DL specific. Every session.</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Bird Dog</td><td>3 × 8 ea</td><td class="xl">BW</td><td class="xnote">—</td><td class="xnote">Always</td></tr>
    </table>
    <div class="dnote">Heavy single + back-off matches your old program. The single builds top-end neural strength. Back-offs build volume under load.</div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="dc">
  <div class="dch"><div class="dcn">Session B — Bench Heavy + Upper</div><div class="badge b-bench">Single ~83% feel / RPE 8 → 4×3 @ 76%</div></div>
  <div class="dcb">
    <table class="xt">
      <tr><th>Exercise</th><th>Sets × Reps</th><th>Load</th><th>RPE</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Bench — build to heavy set</td><td>Warm-up + 1 heavy set</td><td class="xl">~83% feel ≈ 266 lb</td><td class="xnote">RPE 8 — 1–2 reps left</td><td class="xnote">Not a max. Stop at RPE 8. Drives the adaptation.</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Bench — back-off sets</td><td>4 × 3</td><td class="xl">76% = 243 lb</td><td class="xnote">RPE 7</td><td class="xnote">Should feel strong and fast</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Floor Press</td><td>4 × 5</td><td class="xl">70% = 224 lb</td><td class="xnote">RPE 7</td><td class="xnote">No leg drive — forces chest and triceps only</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">OHP (strict)</td><td>4 × 6</td><td class="xl">67% = 131 lb</td><td class="xnote">RPE 7</td><td class="xnote">No leg drive</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Weighted Pull-Up</td><td>4 × 5</td><td class="xl">Moderate</td><td class="xnote">RPE 7</td><td class="xnote">Back thickness supports bench arch</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Close-Grip Bench</td><td>3 × 8</td><td class="xl">66% = 211 lb</td><td class="xnote">RPE 7</td><td class="xnote">Tricep strength = lockout strength</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Tricep Rope Pushdown</td><td>4 × 15</td><td class="xl">Moderate</td><td class="xnote">RPE 7</td><td class="xnote">Lockout volume</td></tr>
    </table>
    <div class="dnote">Floor press every week. Best single accessory for raw pressers — removes the leg drive habit entirely.</div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="dc">
  <div class="dch"><div class="dcn">Session C — C&amp;J + DL + Pull</div><div class="badge b-oly">Single ~83% feel / RPE 8 → 3×2 @ 74%</div></div>
  <div class="dcb">
    <table class="xt">
      <tr><th>Exercise</th><th>Sets × Reps</th><th>Load</th><th>RPE</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Clean &amp; Jerk — build to heavy single</td><td>Warm-up + 1 single</td><td class="xl">~83% feel ≈ 237 lb</td><td class="xnote">RPE 8</td><td class="xnote">Full squat clean, full jerk. Build systematically.</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">C&amp;J — back-off sets</td><td>3 × 2</td><td class="xl">74% = 211 lb</td><td class="xnote">RPE 7</td><td class="xnote">Full movement, smooth</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Clean Pull</td><td>4 × 4</td><td class="xl">90% of single ≈ 213 lb</td><td class="xnote">RPE 7</td><td class="xnote">Triple extension, fast elbows</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Trap Bar Deadlift</td><td>4 × 5</td><td class="xl">68% = 309 lb</td><td class="xnote">RPE 7</td><td class="xnote">Trap bar only through golf season</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Barbell Row (3-sec lower)</td><td>4 × 8</td><td class="xl">63% = 274 lb</td><td class="xnote">RPE 7</td><td class="xnote">Horizontal pull volume</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Lat Pulldown</td><td>3 × 12</td><td class="xl">Moderate</td><td class="xnote">RPE 7</td><td class="xnote">Lat width</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Pallof Press</td><td>3 × 12 ea</td><td class="xl">Cable</td><td class="xnote">—</td><td class="xnote">Anti-rotation, always</td></tr>
    </table>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="dc">
  <div class="dch"><div class="dcn">Session D — Hypertrophy + Beach</div><div class="badge b-beach">Muscle Building · RPE 7–8</div></div>
  <div class="dcb">
    <table class="xt">
      <tr><th>Exercise</th><th>Sets × Reps</th><th>Load</th><th>RPE</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Incline DB Press</td><td>4 × 12</td><td class="xl">Moderate-Heavy</td><td class="xnote">RPE 8</td><td class="xnote">Upper chest priority</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Cable Fly</td><td>3 × 15</td><td class="xl">Light-Mod</td><td class="xnote">RPE 7</td><td class="xnote">Squeeze at peak contraction</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">DB Lateral Raise</td><td>4 × 15</td><td class="xl">Light</td><td class="xnote">RPE 7</td><td class="xnote">Slow, controlled, no cheat</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Rear Delt Fly (cable)</td><td>3 × 20</td><td class="xl">Light</td><td class="xnote">RPE 6</td><td class="xnote">External rotation strength</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">EZ Bar Curl</td><td>4 × 10</td><td class="xl">Moderate</td><td class="xnote">RPE 8</td><td class="xnote">Bicep mass</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Incline DB Curl</td><td>3 × 12</td><td class="xl">Light-Mod</td><td class="xnote">RPE 7</td><td class="xnote">Full stretch at bottom</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Skull Crusher</td><td>4 × 10</td><td class="xl">Moderate</td><td class="xnote">RPE 8</td><td class="xnote">Elbow stays fixed throughout</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Cable Tricep Pushdown</td><td>3 × 15</td><td class="xl">Moderate</td><td class="xnote">RPE 8</td><td class="xnote">Burnout</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="xn">Face Pull</td><td>4 × 20</td><td class="xl">Band</td><td class="xnote">—</td><td class="xnote">Always finish every session with this</td></tr>
    </table>
