<!-- BACK PROTOCOL -->
<div id="spine" class="sec">
  <div class="sh"><h2>Back & SIJ Protocol</h2><span class="sh-tag">Daily · Pre-Golf · Post-Golf · On Shift</span></div>
  <div class="al al-red" style="margin-bottom:20px;">
    <h4>Your Situation — Specific and Honest</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>You're 26. You lift heavy all winter pain-free. Your back hurts from golf, not from lifting. This means your program doesn't need to be stripped down — it needs smarter total load management around golf volume.</li>
      <li>5 rounds/wk × ~80 swings = 400 high-load lumbar rotations per week. Last August you added heavy gym volume on top of that. That crossed the threshold.</li>
      <li>Physio 1–2×/wk is a significant asset. Tell them what you lifted and what you felt. Share this program. They're your real-time feedback loop.</li>
      <li>Root cause: hip rotation availability + glute strength. When hips don't rotate enough, the SI joint compensates. The pre-golf warmup is mechanical prep — not optional.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="grid2">
    <div class="card"><div class="card-tag t-fire">● Every Session — 6 min</div><h3>McGill Big 3</h3>
    <p><span class="t-wh">Modified Curl-Up:</span> 2×10. Hands under lumbar, one knee bent. Minimal flexion. Not a crunch.<br><br>
    <span class="t-wh">Bird Dog:</span> 3×8 each side. Brace before moving. 2-sec hold. Wobble = slow down.<br><br>
    <span class="t-wh">Side Plank:</span> 3×30s each side. Drive hip to ceiling. Progress to 3-point when easy.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><div class="card-tag t-gold">● Before Every Round — 10 min</div><h3>Pre-Golf Warmup</h3>
    <p><span class="t-wh">90/90 Hip Stretch:</span> 2 min each side. Passive — let gravity open the hip.<br><br>
    <span class="t-wh">Hip CARs:</span> 3 slow circles each hip. Full range, zero momentum.<br><br>
    <span class="t-wh">Glute Bridge × 20:</span> Fire SIJ stabilizers before 80 swings.<br><br>
    <span class="t-wh">Half-Kneeling T-Spine Rotation:</span> 10 each side. If it moves in your low back, focus higher.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><div class="card-tag t-grn">● After Every Round — 10 min</div><h3>Post-Round Decompression</h3>
    <p><span class="t-wh">Cat-Cow × 15:</span> Slow and deliberate. Decompress lumbar discs.<br><br>
    <span class="t-wh">Child's Pose:</span> 60s. Passive lumbar unloading.<br><br>
    <span class="t-wh">Piriformis Stretch:</span> 60s each side. Attaches at SI joint — tight piriformis prevents proper SIJ closure.<br><br>
    <span class="t-wh">Standing McKenzie Extension × 10:</span> Hands on low back, extend backward. Counteracts flexion pattern of swing.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><div class="card-tag t-blu">● On Shift — 5 min</div><h3>Station / Hall Routine</h3>
    <p>Bay floor is fine. Between calls.<br><br>
    <span class="t-wh">McGill Big 3:</span> 1 full round.<br><br>
    <span class="t-wh">Hip Flexor Lunge Stretch:</span> 60s each side. SCBA pack forces anterior pelvic tilt — undo it.<br><br>
    <span class="t-wh">Wall Angel × 10:</span> Back flat, arms slide overhead. Counteracts thoracic kyphosis from pack posture.</p></div>
  </div>
  <div class="al al-fire" style="margin-top:8px;">
    <h4>Gym Exercise Rules — Golf Season (May–September)</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>TRAP BAR DEADLIFT replaces conventional from May through September. Only mandatory restriction — everything else stays in.</li>
      <li>FULL SQUAT OLY LIFTS stay in all blocks. The issue is cumulative volume with golf, not the lift itself.</li>
      <li>IF SIJ IS ACTIVELY IRRITATED that week: hang positions only for that week. Short-term, not permanent.</li>
      <li>ANTI-ROTATION core daily: Pallof press, dead bug, Copenhagen plank, suitcase carry. 400 rotations/wk from golf — train the stabilizer, not more rotation.</li>
      <li>GLUTE WORK every session: clamshells, bridges. Weak glutes force the SIJ to stabilize what glutes should. Root of summer flares.</li>
      <li>COMMUNICATE with your physio. Share this document with them. They are your best real-time monitor.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="al al-red">
    <h4>Red Flags — Stop and Assess</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Pain radiating into glute, posterior thigh, or below knee = stop all lifting. Not SIJ — disc or nerve. Physio same week.</li>
      <li>Pain worse in morning for 30+ min before loosening = inflammatory component. Different management needed. See MD.</li>
      <li>Asymmetry in bird dog warmup = mobility only day.</li>
      <li>Pain above 4/10 for 3+ days = physio appointment, don't wait.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- CARDIO -->
<div id="cardio" class="sec">
  <div class="sh"><h2>Cardio & Sprints</h2><span class="sh-tag">Zone 2 · Sprints · Plyo</span></div>
  <div class="al al-grn" style="margin-bottom:18px;">
    <h4>Cardio Philosophy</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Zone 2: 130–145 bpm, conversational. Can't speak in full sentences = too fast. Slow down.</li>
      <li>Running preferred when SIJ healthy — best fat loss tool, highest VO2 stimulus. Switch to bike when SIJ tender. Zero impact beats gritting through it.</li>
      <li>Golf walking 5×/wk in July–August = 25–30 km/wk of Zone 2 already. On those weeks: 2 short runs/bikes max on top.</li>
      <li>Sprints and plyo: Block 4 onward. Every 10–14 days. Before a lift session only. SIJ symptom-free only.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="sh"><h2>Zone 2 Volume by Block</h2><span class="sh-tag">Weekly Totals</span></div>
  <table class="dt" style="margin-bottom:24px;">
    <tr><th>Block</th><th>Standalone/Wk</th><th>Duration</th><th>Golf Walking</th><th>Station Cardio</th><th>Total Approx</th></tr>
    <tr><td class="dt-n">1 Deload</td><td class="dt-v">3×</td><td>22–25 min</td><td>Starting (~3 rounds)</td><td>20 min/shift</td><td>~2.5–3.5 hrs</td></tr>
    <tr><td class="dt-n">2 Build</td><td class="dt-v">2×</td><td>28–35 min</td><td>3–4 rounds (~2–2.5 hrs)</td><td>20 min/shift</td><td>~3.5–4.5 hrs</td></tr>
    <tr><td class="dt-n">3 Peak Golf</td><td class="dt-v">2×</td><td>20–25 min</td><td>5 rounds (~3 hrs)</td><td>20 min/shift</td><td>~4.5–5.5 hrs</td></tr>
    <tr><td class="dt-n">4 Wind-Down</td><td class="dt-v">2×</td><td>30–35 min</td><td>4 rounds (~2.5 hrs)</td><td>20 min/shift</td><td>~4–5 hrs</td></tr>
    <tr><td class="dt-n">5 Rebuild</td><td class="dt-v">2×</td><td>28–32 min</td><td>1–2 rounds</td><td>20 min/shift</td><td>~2–3 hrs</td></tr>
  </table>
  <div class="sh"><h2>Sprint & Plyo Sessions</h2><span class="sh-tag">Blocks 4–5 · Every 10–14 Days · SIJ Clear Only · Before Lift Only</span></div>
  <div class="daygrid">
    <div class="dc">
      <div class="dch"><div class="dcn">Sprint Session A — Flat</div><div class="badge b-sprint">Speed · Quality Not Volume</div></div>
      <div class="dcb">
        <table class="xt">
          <tr><th>Activity</th><th>Sets</th><th>Rest</th><th>Effort</th></tr>
          <tr><td class="xn">Dynamic warmup (A-skips, leg swings, hip circles)</td><td>5 min</td><td class="xl">—</td><td class="xnote">Never skip</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="xn">40m sprint</td><td>3 × 1</td><td class="xl">3 min full</td><td class="xnote">80% effort — build in</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="xn">40m sprint</td><td>3 × 1</td><td class="xl">3 min full</td><td class="xnote">90–95% effort</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="xn">Easy jog cooldown</td><td>5 min</td><td class="xl">—</td><td class="xnote">—</td></tr>
        </table>
        <div class="dnote">Always before a lift. Full 3 min rest between every sprint. This is NOT a conditioning circuit.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="dc">
      <div class="dch"><div class="dcn">Sprint Session B — Hills</div><div class="badge b-sprint">Lower Hamstring Risk</div></div>
      <div class="dcb">
        <table class="xt">
          <tr><th>Activity</th><th>Sets</th><th>Rest</th><th>Effort</th></tr>
          <tr><td class="xn">Hill sprint (6–8% grade, 30m)</td><td>3 × 1</td><td class="xl">3 min</td><td class="xnote">90%</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="xn">Hill sprint (same)</td><td>3 × 1</td><td class="xl">3 min</td><td class="xnote">95%, walk back down</td></tr>
        </table>
        <div class="dnote">Less hamstring strain. Good when lower body is loaded from squatting. Assault bike 10-sec all-outs × 8 (3 min rest) = indoor equivalent.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="dc">
      <div class="dch"><div class="dcn">Plyo Session</div><div class="badge b-sprint">Power + Athleticism</div></div>
      <div class="dcb">
        <table class="xt">
          <tr><th>Exercise</th><th>Sets × Reps</th><th>Rest</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
          <tr><td class="xn">Box Jump (24")</td><td>4 × 5</td><td class="xl">90s full</td><td class="xnote">Land soft, reset stance between reps</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="xn">Broad Jump</td><td>3 × 4</td><td class="xl">Full</td><td class="xnote">Max effort each rep</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="xn">Single-Leg Hop (forward)</td><td>3 × 5 ea</td><td class="xl">60s</td><td class="xnote">Stick landing</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="xn">Med Ball Rotational Throw (wall)</td><td>3 × 8 ea</td><td class="xl">45s</td><td class="xnote">Golf-specific rotational power. Hip-driven.</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="xn">Med Ball Slam</td><td>3 × 8</td><td class="xl">45s</td><td class="xnote">Full body power expression</td></tr>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="dc">
      <div class="dch"><div class="dcn">All Cardio Tools</div><div class="badge b-cardio">Options by Situation</div></div>
      <div class="dcb">
        <table class="xt">
          <tr><th>Tool</th><th>Best For</th><th>SIJ</th></tr>
          <tr><td class="xn">Outdoor run</td><td class="xnote">Recomp + VO2 — primary tool</td><td class="xnote">Perfect when SIJ healthy</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="xn">Outdoor bike</td><td class="xnote">SIJ-safe Zone 2</td><td class="xnote">Zero impact — anytime</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="xn">Rowing erg</td><td class="xnote">Full body Zone 2</td><td class="xnote">No spinal impact</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="xn">Assault bike</td><td class="xnote">Zone 2 + sprints</td><td class="xnote">Best indoor sprint tool</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="xn">Ski erg</td><td class="xnote">Posterior chain Zone 2</td><td class="xnote">No impact</td></tr>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- NUTRITION -->
<div id="nutrition" class="sec">
  <div class="sh"><h2>Nutrition & Recomp</h2><span class="sh-tag">16% → 13% · Alcohol Included · Honest Plan</span></div>
  <div class="al al-gold" style="margin-bottom:16px;">
    <h4>The Honest Alcohol Assessment</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>2–6 drinks, 1–2 nights/wk. Lower end slows recomp minimally. Upper end (6 drinks × 2 nights) adds 2–3 weeks and worsens SIJ recovery for 24–48 hrs after each session.</li>
      <li>On drinking nights: drop dietary fat to 20–25g. Keep carbs and protein normal. Alcohol + high fat is what gets stored efficiently.</li>
      <li>4+ drinks acutely raises inflammatory markers for 24–48 hrs. Avoid heavy nights before a 5-round golf week or heavy Oly session.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="sh"><h2>Body Composition Timeline</h2><span class="sh-tag">Realistic Projections</span></div>
  <div style="margin-bottom:24px;">
    <div class="bcbar"><div class="bcl">Start — May 2025</div><div class="bct"><div class="bcf" style="width:80%;background:var(--red);"></div></div><div class="bcn">~16% BF · 207 lbs · ~33 lbs fat · ~174 lbs lean</div></div>
    <div class="bcbar"><div class="bcl">Target — July 2025 (8–10 weeks)</div><div class="bct"><div class="bcf" style="width:63%;background:var(--gold);"></div></div><div class="bcn">~13% BF · ~201–202 lbs · -5–6 lbs fat · lean mass protected via 190g+ protein + creatine daily</div></div>
    <div class="bcbar"><div class="bcl">Maintain — July through October</div><div class="bct"><div class="bcf" style="width:63%;background:var(--grn);"></div></div><div class="bcn">Eat at TDEE. Do not diet through peak golf season. SIJ heals better when fueled.</div></div>
    <div class="bcbar"><div class="bcl">Winter Bulk — November → April 2026</div><div class="bct"><div class="bcf" style="width:70%;background:var(--blu);"></div></div><div class="bcn">+300–400 cal/day surplus. Target ~14–15% BF entering May 2026 with higher absolute strength.</div></div>
  </div>
  <div class="lg">
    <div class="lc"><h3 style="color:var(--fire);">Daily Calories — Recomp</h3><ul>
      <li>Heavy lift day: 2,800–2,950 cal</li><li>Golf + no lift: 2,700–2,850 cal</li><li>Shift day: 2,400–2,550 cal</li>
      <li>Rest / light cardio: 2,300–2,400 cal</li><li>Drinking night: ~2,400, fat under 25g, protein 190g+</li>
      <li>Floor: never below 2,200 cal</li><li>Avg deficit target: ~400 cal/day = ~0.7 lbs fat/wk</li></ul></div>
    <div class="lc"><h3 style="color:var(--gold);">Protein Targets</h3><ul>
      <li>On deficit: 190g/day minimum</li><li>Optimal: 200–215g/day</li>
      <li>Post-golf: 40–50g within 60 min of finishing</li><li>Pre-bed: 30–40g slow protein — connective tissue repairs overnight</li>
      <li>Shift days: prep snacks for the hall</li><li>Before drinking: full protein meal first</li></ul></div>
    <div class="lc"><h3 style="color:var(--grn);">Supplement Stack</h3><ul>
      <li>Creatine monohydrate: 5g/day always — protects lean mass on deficit</li>
      <li>Omega-3 (EPA+DHA): 3g/day — anti-inflammatory, directly benefits SIJ</li>
      <li>Vitamin D3 + K2: 3,000–4,000 IU D3 — shift workers chronically deficient</li>
      <li>Collagen + Vit C: 10g collagen + 50mg C pre-training — ligament/tendon support</li>
      <li>Magnesium glycinate: 300–400mg before bed — sleep depth on shift nights</li>
      <li>Electrolytes on hot golf days</li></ul></div>
    <div class="lc"><h3 style="color:var(--blu);">Sleep & Recovery</h3><ul>
      <li>Post-shift: 7–9 hrs before any heavy Oly or squat session</li>
      <li>Sleep deprivation raises cortisol → raises inflammation → worsens SIJ. Disrupted sleep after shifts is a bigger SIJ risk than any lift in this program.</li>
      <li>Golf season: protect 8 hrs sleep over any training goal</li>
      <li>SIJ flare-up: ice 15 min × 3/day. NOT heat in first 48 hrs.</li>
      <li>Physio: tell them what you lifted and what you felt. That loop is your biggest recovery advantage.</li></ul></div>
    <div class="lc"><h3 style="color:var(--fire);">Hydration</h3><ul>
      <li>Heavy golf days Jul–Aug: 3.5–5L minimum</li><li>Lift days: 2.5–3L minimum</li>
      <li>Shift days: 2.5–3L — dehydration under gear compounds injury risk</li>
      <li>Dehydration worsens disc hydration and SI joint lubrication directly</li>
      <li>Alcohol: add 500ml water per 2 drinks overnight</li>
      <li>Electrolytes on rounds over 25°C — sodium first</li></ul></div>
    <div class="lc"><h3 style="color:var(--purp);">Golf Season Maintenance</h3><ul>
      <li>Deficit OFF once recomp complete. Eat at TDEE.</li>
      <li>Golf walking 5×/wk burns ~1,400–1,800 cal/wk. Maintenance calories are high — eat to it.</li>
      <li>Underfueling through peak golf = higher SIJ flare risk. Not worth it.</li>
      <li>Heavy golf day maintenance: 3,000–3,200 cal</li>
      <li>Protein stays at 190g+ even in maintenance</li></ul></div>
  </div>
</div>

<script>
function S(id,btn){
  document.querySelectorAll('.sec').forEach(s=>s.classList.remove('on'));
  document.querySelectorAll('.nb').forEach(b=>b.classList.remove('on'));
  document.getElementById(id).classList.add('on');
  btn.classList.add('on');
  window.scrollTo({top:0,behavior:'smooth'});
}
function gP(pid){
  document.querySelectorAll('.sec').forEach(s=>s.classList.remove('on'));
  document.querySelectorAll('.nb').forEach(b=>b.classList.toggle('on',b.textContent.trim()==='Workouts'));
  document.getElementById('workouts').classList.add('on');
  document.querySelectorAll('.pd').forEach(p=>p.classList.remove('on'));
  document.querySelectorAll('.pb').forEach(b=>b.classList.remove('on'));
  const t=document.getElementById(pid);
  if(t)t.classList.add('on');
  document.querySelectorAll('.pb').forEach(b=>{
    if(b.getAttribute('onclick')&&b.getAttribute('onclick').includes("'"+pid+"'"))b.classList.add('on');
  });
}
function sP(pid,btn){
  document.querySelectorAll('.pd').forEach(p=>p.classList.remove('on'));
  document.querySelectorAll('.pb').forEach(b=>b.classList.remove('on'));
  const t=document.getElementById(pid);
  if(t)t.classList.add('on');
  btn.classList.add('on');
  const fw=t&&t.querySelector('.wd');if(fw)fw.classList.add('on');
  const ft=t&&t.querySelector('.wt');if(ft)ft.classList.add('on');
}
function sW(phid,wid,btn){
  const ph=document.getElementById(phid);
  if(!ph)return;
  ph.querySelectorAll(':scope>.wd').forEach(w=>w.classList.remove('on'));
  const t=document.getElementById(phid+'-'+wid);
  if(t)t.classList.add('on');
  const tabs=ph.querySelector('.wtabs');
  if(tabs)tabs.querySelectorAll('.wt').forEach(b=>b.classList.remove('on'));
  btn.classList.add('on');
}
</script>
</body>
</html>
